The paper also mentions the use of game-state representations, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics), making it the third likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed framework in human-computer interaction, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), making it the fifth likely category.
